<p>
   The UC College Prep AP Computer Science course is composed of 
   several <b>units</b>.  Each unit is composed of two or more course <b>lessons</b>.  Each lesson contains a variety of Sections and Steps.
</p>
<p>
   Each lesson is designed to be completed in about a week, involving an estimated four hours of 
   supervised work and a variable amount of unsupervised work.
</p>
<p> A list of the units and lessons is shown <a href="syllabus.php">Syllabus</a>, available in the Course Resources area.</p>